                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-26T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. Your July 24, 10 p.m. Regarding Section 2 of the Liberian proposal is there
                    any other law which could, if necessary, be invoked by the commission in order
                    to strengthen its hand in dealing with witnesses.</p>
                <p>Please cable reply with your comments and suggestions following which the
                    Department will instruct you further.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
